{"id":"glory","term":"Glory","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(Heb. kabhod; Gr. doxa). (1.) Abundance, wealth, treasure, and hence honour (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 49:12\">Ps. 49:12</a>); glory (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 31:1\">Gen. 31:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 4:8\">Matt. 4:8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 21:24\">Rev. 21:24</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 21:26\">26</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) Honour, dignity (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 3:13\">1 Kings 3:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 2:7\">Heb. 2:7</a> <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 1:24\">1 Pet. 1:24</a>); of God (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 19:1\">Ps. 19:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 29:1\">29:1</a>); of the mind or heart (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 49:6\">Gen. 49:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 7:5\">Ps. 7:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 2:46\">Acts 2:46</a>).</p>\n<p>(3.) Splendour, brightness, majesty (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 45:13\">Gen. 45:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 4:5\">Isa. 4:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 22:11\">Acts 22:11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Corinthians 3:7\">2 Cor. 3:7</a>); of Jehovah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 59:19\">Isa. 59:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 60:1\">60:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Thessalonians 1:9\">2 Thess. 1:9</a>).</p>\n<p>(4.) The glorious moral attributes, the infinite perfections of God (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 40:5\">Isa. 40:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 7:2\">Acts 7:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 1:23\">Rom. 1:23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 9:23\">9:23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ephesians 1:12\">Eph. 1:12</a>). Jesus is the “brightness of the Father’s glory” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 1:3\">Heb. 1:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 1:14\">John 1:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 2:11\">2:11</a>).</p>\n<p>(5.) The bliss of heaven (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 2:7\">Rom. 2:7</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:10\">10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 5:2\">5:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 8:18\">8:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 2:10\">Heb. 2:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 5:1\">1 Pet. 5:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 5:10\">10</a>).</p>\n<p>(6.) The phrase “Give glory to God” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 7:19\">Josh. 7:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 13:16\">Jer. 13:16</a>) is a Hebrew idiom meaning, “Confess your sins.” The words of the Jews to the blind man, “Give God the praise” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 9:24\">John 9:24</a>), are an adjuration to confess. They are equivalent to, “Confess that you are an impostor,” “Give God the glory by speaking the truth;” for they denied that a miracle had been wrought.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Psalms 49:12","Genesis 31:1","Matthew 4:8","Revelation 21:24","Revelation 21:26","1 Kings 3:13","Hebrews 2:7","1 Peter 1:24","Psalms 19:1","Psalms 29:1","Genesis 49:6","Psalms 7:5","Acts 2:46","Genesis 45:13","Isaiah 4:5","Acts 22:11","2 Corinthians 3:7","Isaiah 59:19","Isaiah 60:1","2 Thessalonians 1:9","Isaiah 40:5","Acts 7:2","Romans 1:23","Romans 9:23","Ephesians 1:12","Hebrews 1:3","John 1:14","John 2:11","Romans 2:7","Genesis 1:10","Genesis 5:2","Genesis 8:18","Hebrews 2:10","1 Peter 5:1","1 Peter 5:10","Joshua 7:19","Jeremiah 13:16","John 9:24"]}